# Backend Development (next-forge)

TypeScript only. Governance: `skills/next-forge/references/architecture.md`, `AGENTS.md`. Security: `backend-security.mdc`.

## Next.js docs — MCP, not memory

`nextjs-docs://llms-index` → `nextjs_docs`. Dev server: `nextjs_index` → `nextjs_call`. See `nextjs-mcp-quality.mdc`.

## Execution layers

| Layer | Path | Responsibility |
|-------|------|----------------|
| Domain packages | `packages/*` | Auth, database, payments, etc. — `server-only` exports |
| Server Actions | `apps/app/app/actions/` | In-app mutations; auth via `@repo/auth/server` |
| Route Handlers | `apps/app/app/api/`, `apps/api/` | Webhooks, external HTTP, cron |
| Server Components | `apps/app/app/` | Data fetch, layout — default pattern |

```typescript
'use server'

import { auth } from '@repo/auth/server'

export async function searchUsers(query: string) {
  const { orgId } = await auth()
  if (!orgId) throw new Error('Not logged in')
  // delegate to @repo/* packages
}
```

## Server Actions vs Route Handlers

- **Server Actions** — in-app mutations and forms (`'use server'`)
- **Route Handlers** — webhooks, external HTTP; never colocate `route.ts` with `page.tsx`
- Business logic lives in `@repo/*` packages — actions stay thin

## Cache invalidation

| API | Where | When |
|-----|-------|------|
| `updateTag` | Server Actions only | User must see their write immediately |
| `revalidateTag` | Actions or Route Handlers | Stale-while-revalidate OK |
| `revalidatePath` | Actions or Route Handlers | Route-wide refresh; prefer tags |
| `refresh()` | Server Actions | Client router UI only |

Tagged reads: `cacheTag` inside `"use cache"` helpers with `cacheLife`. MCP path: `/docs/app/getting-started/revalidating`.

## Anti-patterns

```typescript
// ❌ DB client imported in client component
'use client'
import { database } from '@repo/database'

// ❌ Cache before mutation succeeds
revalidatePath('/items')
await createItem(body)

// ✅ Server-only package + cache after success
const item = await createItem(body)
revalidatePath('/items')
```

